                            <comment id="14971422" author="romseygeek" created="Fri, 23 Oct 2015 17:33:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Throwing NPE is fine, I think, but we should do that when add() is called, rather than later during processing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14980067" author="markus17" created="Thu, 29 Oct 2015 08:55:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Agreed! The the call immediately throws NPE, it is clear enough.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15021826" author="romseygeek" created="Mon, 23 Nov 2015 09:22:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch adding Objects.requireNonNull() checks to the various UpdateRequest.add() methods, and some javadoc as well for good measure.  I&apos;ll get this in before the 5.4 branch is created.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
